SIMPLE: impudent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impudent
<hw>Im"pu*dent</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m"p⟦usl⟧*d⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>impudens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets>
not + <ets>pudens</ets> ashamed, modest, p. pr. of <ets>pudere</ets> to
feel shame: cf. F. <ets>impudent</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Behaving
boldly, with contempt or disregard for propriety in behavior toward
others; unblushingly forward; impertinent; saucy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>More than <qex>impudent</qex> sauciness.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When we behold an angel, not to fear⟦br⟧
Is to be <qex>impudent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacking modesty; shameless.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Shameless; audacious; brazen; bold-faced; pert;
immodest; rude; saucy; impertinent; insolent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impudently</ent>⟦br⟧
